HEADWORD: Prestimony
<hw>Pres"ti*mo*ny</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>praestimonium</ets>, fr. L. <ets>praestare</ets> to furnish,
supply: cf. F. <ets>prestimonie</ets>. See <er>Prest</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <fld>(Canon Law)</fld> <def>A fund for the support
of a priest, without the title of a benefice. The patron in the
collator.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

